      "output": "<path>C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Documents\\cognitive-taxonomy-site\\index.html</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: <!DOCTYPE html>\n2: <html lang=\"en\">\n3: <head>\n4: <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n5: <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n6: <meta name=\"theme-color\" content=\"#0f0f0f\">\n7: <meta name=\"color-scheme\" content=\"dark\">\n8: <title>Cognitive Taxonomy Protocol — Rewire How You Read Code</title>\n9: <meta name=\"description\" content=\"A five-colour taxonomy that rewires how you read code. From line-by-line scanning to instant pattern recognition.\">\n10: <link rel=\"preconnect\" href=\"https://fonts.googleapis.com\">\n11: <link rel=\"preconnect\" href=\"https://fonts.gstatic.com\" crossorigin>\n12: <link href=\"https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;500;600;700;800&family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@400;500;600&display=swap\" rel=\"stylesheet\">\n13: <link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"css/style.css\">\n14: </head>\n15: <body>\n16: \n17: <!-- Skip to content (accessibility) -->\n18: <a href=\"#main-content\" class=\"skip-link\">Skip to main content</a>\n19: \n20: <!-- ── Navigation ──────────────────────────────────────────────── -->\n21: <nav class=\"nav\" role=\"navigation\" aria-label=\"Main navigation\">\n22:   <div class=\"nav-inner\">\n23:     <a href=\"index.html\" class=\"nav-brand\">\n24:       <span class=\"nav-logo\">\n25:         <span class=\"nav-logo-dot\" style=\"background:var(--blue)\"></span>\n26:         <span class=\"nav-logo-dot\" style=\"background:var(--green)\"></span>\n27:         <span class=\"nav-logo-dot\" style=\"background:var(--orange)\"></span>\n28:         <span class=\"nav-logo-dot\" style=\"background:var(--red)\"></span>\n29:         <span class=\"nav-logo-dot\" style=\"background:var(--purple)\"></span>\n30:       </span>\n31:       CTP\n32:     </a>\n33:     <button class=\"nav-toggle\" aria-label=\"Toggle navigation\">\n34:       <span></span><span></span><span></span>\n35:     </button>\n36:     <ul class=\"nav-links\">\n37:       <li><a href=\"index.html\" class=\"nav-link active\">Home</a></li>\n38:       <li><a href=\"about.html\" class=\"nav-link\">About</a></li>\n39:       <li><a href=\"install.html\" class=\"nav-link\">Install</a></li>\n40:       <li><a href=\"demo.html\" class=\"nav-link\">Demo</a></li>\n41:       <li><a href=\"llm-demo.html\" class=\"nav-link\">LLM Demo</a></li>\n42:       <li><a href=\"wiki.html\" class=\"nav-link\">Wiki</a></li>\n43:       <li><a href=\"install.html\" class=\"nav-cta\">Get Started</a></li>\n44:     </ul>\n45:   </div>\n46: </nav>\n47: \n48: <main id=\"main-content\">\n49: <!-- ── Hero ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->\n50: <section class=\"hero\">\n51:   <div class=\"container\">\n52:     <div class=\"hero-eyebrow\">\n53:       <span class=\"hero-eyebrow-dot\"></span>\n54:       Open Source &bull; VS Code Extension\n55:     </div>\n56:     <h1>Cognitive Taxonomy Protocol</h1>\n57:     <p class=\"hero-subtitle\">\n58:       Rewire how you read code. Five colours. One taxonomy.<br>\n59:       From line-by-line scanning to instant pattern recognition.\n60:     </p>\n61:     <div class=\"hero-actions\">\n62:       <a href=\"install.html\" class=\"btn btn-primary\">Install Extension</a>\n63:       <a href=\"demo.html\" class=\"btn btn-secondary\">See It In Action</a>\n64:     </div>\n65: \n66:     <!-- Stats -->\n67:     <div class=\"stats-grid\">\n68:       <div class=\"stat\">\n69:         <div class=\"stat-value\" data-value=\"5\">0</div>\n70:         <div class=\"stat-label\">Colour Categories</div>\n71:       </div>\n72:       <div class=\"stat\">\n73:         <div class=\"stat-value\" data-value=\"82\" data-suffix=\"%\">0</div>\n74:         <div class=\"stat-label\">Faster Comprehension</div>\n75:       </div>\n76:       <div class=\"stat\">\n77:         <div class=\"stat-value\" data-value=\"4\">0</div>\n78:         <div class=\"stat-label\">Data Flow Views</div>\n79:       </div>\n80:       <div class=\"stat\">\n81:         <div class=\"stat-value\" data-value=\"5\">0</div>\n82:         <div class=\"stat-label\">Domain Detection</div>\n83:       </div>\n84:     </div>\n85:   </div>\n86: </section>\n87: \n88: <!-- ── Taxonomy Cards ──────────────────────────────────────────── -->\n89: <section class=\"section\" id=\"taxonomy\">\n90:   <div class=\"container\">\n91:     <h2>The Five-Colour Taxonomy</h2>\n92:     <p class=\"section-subtitle\">Every line of code falls into one of five categories. Your brain learns to recognise them instantly.</p>\n93: \n94:     <div class=\"taxonomy-grid\">\n95:       <div class=\"tax-card\" style=\"border-left: 4px solid var(--blue);\">\n96:         <div class=\"tax-header\">\n97:           <span class=\"tax-dot\" style=\"background: var(--blue);\"></span>\n98:           <span class=\"tax-name\">Blueprint</span>\n99:         </div>\n100:         <p class=\"tax-desc\">What the code needs to remember. Like furniture in a house.</p>\n101:         <div class=\"tax-example\">\n102:           <code>class Option:<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;strike: float<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;expiry: date</code>\n103:         </div>\n104:       </div>\n105: \n106:       <div class=\"tax-card\" style=\"border-left: 4px solid var(--green);\">\n107:         <div class=\"tax-header\">\n108:           <span class=\"tax-dot\" style=\"background: var(--green);\"></span>\n109:           <span class=\"tax-name\">Plumbing</span>\n110:         </div>\n111:         <p class=\"tax-desc\">Bringing things from outside. Like a delivery truck.</p>\n112:         <div class=\"tax-example\">\n113:           <code>import pandas as pd<br>from flask import Flask</code>\n114:         </div>\n115:       </div>\n116: \n117:       <div class=\"tax-card\" style=\"border-left: 4px solid var(--orange);\">\n118:         <div class=\"tax-header\">\n119:           <span class=\"tax-dot\" style=\"background: var(--orange);\"></span>\n120:           <span class=\"tax-name\">Transaction</span>\n121:         </div>\n122:         <p class=\"tax-desc\">What the code actually does. Like people cooking and cleaning.</p>\n123:         <div class=\"tax-example\">\n124:           <code>price = calculate_price(<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;option, market_data<br>)</code>\n125:         </div>\n126:       </div>\n127: \n128:       <div class=\"tax-card\" style=\"border-left: 4px solid var(--red);\">\n129:         <div class=\"tax-header\">\n130:           <span class=\"tax-dot\" style=\"background: var(--red);\"></span>\n131:           <span class=\"tax-name\">Constraint</span>\n132:         </div>\n133:         <p class=\"tax-desc\">Rules that must never be broken. Like locks on doors.</p>\n134:         <div class=\"tax-example\">\n135:           <code>if price &lt; 0:<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;raise ValueError(<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\"Price must be positive\"<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;)</code>\n136:         </div>\n137:       </div>\n138: \n139:       <div class=\"tax-card\" style=\"border-left: 4px solid var(--purple);\">\n140:         <div class=\"tax-header\">\n141:           <span class=\"tax-dot\" style=\"background: var(--purple);\"></span>\n142:           <span class=\"tax-name\">Pedagogy</span>\n143:         </div>\n144:         <p class=\"tax-desc\">Notes for yourself later. Like labels on boxes.</p>\n145:         <div class=\"tax-example\">\n146:           <code># Calculates the price of<br># a European call option<br># using Black-Scholes</code>\n147:         </div>\n148:       </div>\n149:     </div>\n150:   </div>\n151: </section>\n152: \n153: <!-- ── Features ──────────────────────────────────────────────── -->\n154: <section class=\"section section--alt\" id=\"features\">\n155:   <div class=\"container\">\n156:     <h2>What CTP Does</h2>\n157:     <p class=\"section-subtitle\">Not just syntax highlighting. Understanding.</p>\n158: \n159:     <div class=\"features-grid\">\n160:       <div class=\"feature-card\">\n161:         <div class=\"feature-icon\">🔍</div>\n162:         <h3>AST-Based Classifier</h3>\n163:         <p>Parses Python code using the AST (Abstract Syntax Tree). Understands structure, not just text.</p>\n164:       </div>\n165:       <div class=\"feature-card\">\n166:         <div class=\"feature-icon\">💬</div>\n167:         <h3>Plain English Tooltips</h3>\n168:         <p>Hover over any line. Get a plain-English explanation of what it does, why it matters, and what breaks without it.</p>\n169:       </div>\n170:       <div class=\"feature-card\">\n171:         <div class=\"feature-icon\">🔀</div>\n172:         <h3>Data Flow Visualization</h3>\n173:         <p>See how data moves through your code. Four views: ASCII, Mini, Mermaid, SVG.</p>\n174:       </div>\n175:       <div class=\"feature-card\">\n176:         <div class=\"feature-icon\">👃</div>\n177:         <h3>Code Smell Detection</h3>\n178:         <p>Automatically finds magic numbers, long methods, deep nesting, and missing validation.</p>\n179:       </div>\n180:       <div class=\"feature-card\">\n181:         <div class=\"feature-icon\">🌐</div>\n182:         <h3>Domain Detection</h3>\n183:         <p>Auto-detects finance, networking, web, data science, and automation. Uses the right terminology.</p>\n184:       </div>\n185:       <div class=\"feature-card\">\n186:         <div class=\"feature-icon\">📊</div>\n187:         <h3>Sidebar Dashboard</h3>\n188:         <p>Architecture map, category breakdown, balance scores, and line-by-line navigator.</p>\n189:       </div>\n190:     </div>\n191:   </div>\n192: </section>\n193: \n194: <!-- ── CTA ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->\n195: <section class=\"section cta-section\">\n196:   <div class=\"container\" style=\"text-align: center;\">\n197:     <h2>Ready to Rewire How You Read Code?</h2>\n198:     <p class=\"section-subtitle\">Install the extension. Open a Python file. Press Ctrl+Shift+T.</p>\n199:     <a href=\"install.html\" class=\"btn btn-primary\">Install Now</a>\n200:   </div>\n201: </section>\n202: </main>\n203: \n204: <!-- ── Footer ──────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->\n205: <footer class=\"footer\" role=\"contentinfo\">\n206:   <div class=\"container\">\n207:     <div class=\"footer-inner\">\n208:       <div class=\"footer-brand\">\n209:         <span class=\"nav-logo\">\n210:           <span class=\"nav-logo-dot\" style=\"background:var(--blue)\"></span>\n211:           <span class=\"nav-logo-dot\" style=\"background:var(--green)\"></span>\n212:           <span class=\"nav-logo-dot\" style=\"background:var(--orange)\"></span>\n213:           <span class=\"nav-logo-dot\" style=\"background:var(--red)\"></span>\n214:           <span class=\"nav-logo-dot\" style=\"background:var(--purple)\"></span>\n215:         </span>\n216:         <span>Cognitive Taxonomy Protocol</span>\n217:       </div>\n218:       <div class=\"footer-links\">\n219:         <a href=\"about.html\">About</a>\n220:         <a href=\"install.html\">Install</a>\n221:         <a href=\"demo.html\">Demo</a>\n222:         <a href=\"#\">GitHub</a>\n223:       </div>\n224:     </div>\n225:     <div class=\"footer-copy\">&copy; 2026 CTP. Open source under MIT License.</div>\n226:   </div>\n227: </footer>\n228: \n229: <script src=\"js/nav.js\"></script>\n230: </body>\n231: </html>\n\n(End of file - total 231 lines)\n</content>",
