      "type": "answer",
      "text": "Based on the Frappe Bench logs, I can see the core issue:\n\n**Problem:** The Frappe app `fg_firstgens_app` was created but is not properly registered in the Frappe Bench environment. The error `ModuleNotFoundError: No module named 'fg_firstgens_app'` indicates the app needs to be properly installed into the site.\n\n**Solution:**\n\n```bash\n# Navigate to your Frappe bench directory\ncd /home/andiekobbie/frappe-bench\n\n# Install the app into the site\nbench --site firstgens.localhost install-app fg_firstgens_app\n```\n\n**Steps to fix:**\n\n1. **Ensure the app is properly structured:**\n   - The app directory `/home/andiekobbie/frappe-bench/apps/fg_firstgens_app` should contain:\n     - `__init__.py`\n     - `hooks.py`\n     - `setup.py`\n     - `site_config.json` (if needed)\n\n2. **Install the app:**\n   ```bash\n   cd /home/andiekobbie/frappe-bench\n   bench --site firstgens.localhost install-app fg_firstgens_app\n   ```\n\n3. **Restart services:**\n   ```bash\n   bench restart\n   ```\n\n4. **Verify installation:**\n   ```bash\n   curl http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/method/frappe.ping\n   ```\n\nThe app is created but not being recognized by Frappe because it's missing proper hooks registration and hasn't been installed into the site. The `bench install-app` command should resolve this by registering the app in Frappe's app registry.",
      "timestamp": 1781964078768
    },
