      "type": "answer",
      "text": "The issue is in the Frappe app structure. Based on the logs, the `fg_firstgens_app` was created but lacks the proper Python package structure.\n\n**Root Cause:**\nThe app directory at `/home/andiekobbie/frappe-bench/apps/fg_firstgens_app` is missing essential Python files that Frappe needs to recognize it as an installed app.\n\n**Fix:**\n\n1. **Stop Frappe services:**\n   ```bash\n   cd /home/andiekobbie/frappe-bench\n   bench stop\n   ```\n\n2. **Remove the incorrectly created app:**\n   ```bash\n   rm -rf /home/andiekobbie/frappe-bench/apps/fg_firstgens_app\n   ```\n\n3. **Create the app properly using bench:**\n   ```bash\n   cd /home/andiekobbie/frappe-bench\n   bench new-app fg_firstgens_app\n   ```\n\n4. **When prompted, use these values:**\n   - App Title: Fg Firstgens App\n   - App Description: Community platform for first-generation students\n   - Publisher: FirstGens\n   - Email: admin@firstgens.test\n   - License: mit\n   - Frappe Version: version-15\n   - Install now: y\n\n5. **Start Frappe services:**\n   ```bash\n   bench start\n   ```\n\nThe `bench new-app` command automatically creates the proper structure with:\n- `__init__.py` (empty)\n- `hooks.py` (with basic hooks)\n- `setup.py`\n- All necessary configuration files\n\nThis ensures the app is properly integrated into the Frappe framework and can be installed into sites without the `ModuleNotFoundError`.",
