      "text": "I can see from your logs that your Frappe Bench setup is on a Linux system. The issues are clear:\n\n**Problems identified:**\n1. You created the app with `--no-git` flag, which bypasses proper initialization\n2. Frappe v11 is end-of-life (needs v15+ for compatibility)\n3. Missing essential app files: `__init__.py`, `hooks.py`, `setup.py`, etc.\n4. `bench stop` command doesn't exist in Frappe v11\n\n**Solution:**\n\n```bash\n# Navigate to your Frappe bench directory\ncd /home/andiekobbie/frappe-bench\n\n# 1. Stop services (if available) or restart\nbench restart || pkill -f frappe || echo \"No running Frappe services\"\n\n# 2. Remove the broken app\nrm -rf /home/andiekobbie/frappe-bench/apps/fg_firstgens_app\n\n# 3. Create app properly (without --no-git)\nbench new-app fg_firstgens_app\n\n# 4. When prompted, use:\n#    App Title: Fg Firstgens App\n#    App Description: Community platform for first-generation students\n#    Publisher: FirstGens\n#    Email: admin@firstgens.test\n#    License: mit\n#    Frappe Version: version-15 (Recommended)\n#    Install now: y\n\n# 5. Install the app\nbench --site firstgens.localhost install-app fg_firstgens_app\n\n# 6. Start services\nbench start\n```\n\n**The key difference:**\n- `bench new-app fg_firstgens_app` creates the proper structure with all necessary files\n- `bench new-app fg_firstgens_app --no-git` creates a minimal structure that lacks essential files\n\nWithout `--no-git`, the app will include:\n- `__init__.py`\n- `hooks.py` \n- `setup.py`\n- `app.json`\n- And other configuration files needed for Frappe integration\n\nThis should resolve the `ModuleNotFoundError` and get your Frappe site working properly.",
