      "output": "<path>C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\community-launchpad-proto\\README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # FirstGens Community — Platform Prototype & Blueprint\n2: \n3: > **First-generation university students deserve a community platform that truly understands them.**\n4: > This repository is both the clickable prototype (run it today) *and* the complete technical blueprint for the production Frappe-powered platform it will become.\n5: \n6: ---\n7: \n8: ## Table of Contents\n9: \n10: 1. [What this is](#1-what-this-is)\n11: 2. [What this will become](#2-what-this-will-become)\n12: 3. [Running it right now](#3-running-it-right-now)\n13: 4. [Architecture overview](#4-architecture-overview)\n14: 5. [User journeys — Mermaid flowcharts](#5-user-journeys--mermaid-flowcharts)\n15:    - 5.1 [New member onboarding](#51-new-member-onboarding)\n16:    - 5.2 [Posting in a Space](#52-posting-in-a-space)\n17:    - 5.3 [Mentor match flow](#53-mentor-match-flow)\n18:    - 5.4 [Event RSVP flow](#54-event-rsvp-flow)\n19:    - 5.5 [Course enrolment & progress](#55-course-enrolment--progress)\n20:    - 5.6 [Direct messages (Raven)](#56-direct-messages-raven)\n21:    - 5.7 [Safeguarding & moderation pipeline](#57-safeguarding--moderation-pipeline)\n22:    - 5.8 [Paywall / membership gating](#58-paywall--membership-gating)\n23:    - 5.9 [Gamification & badge award](#59-gamification--badge-award)\n24:    - 5.10 [Weekly community digest](#510-weekly-community-digest)\n25:    - 5.11 [Full platform data flow](#511-full-platform-data-flow)\n26: 6. [Project structure](#6-project-structure)\n27: 7. [Pages & routes](#7-pages--routes)\n28: 8. [Mock data & schema contract](#8-mock-data--schema-contract)\n29: 9. [The Frappe DNA — why this stack](#9-the-frappe-dna--why-this-stack)\n30: 10. [The Circle.so DNA — feature parity map](#10-the-circleso-dna--feature-parity-map)\n31: 11. [Documentation index](#11-documentation-index)\n32: 12. [How long to production?](#12-how-long-to-production)\n33: 13. [Contributing & branch rules](#13-contributing--branch-rules)\n34: \n35: ---\n36: \n37: ## 1. What this is\n38: \n39: **A high-fidelity, clickable UX/UI prototype** for a community platform supporting first-generation university students in the UK. It exists so stakeholders, designers, and prospective users can:\n40: \n41: - Click through realistic end-to-end flows before a single production database row is written\n42: - Validate the information architecture\n43: - Sign off UX decisions as Gherkin scenarios (see [`docs/09_GHERKIN_UX_SCENARIOS.md`](docs/09_GHERKIN_UX_SCENARIOS.md))\n44: - Confirm that the data model is schema-faithful to the real Frappe backend\n45: \n46: **Tech stack (prototype only):**\n47: \n48: | Layer | Choice | Why |\n49: |---|---|---|\n50: | UI framework | Vue 3 + TypeScript | Type-safe components that mirror Frappe shapes |\n\n(Showing lines 1-50 of 790. Use offset=51 to continue.)\n</content>",
