      "output": "<path>C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\community-launchpad-proto\\README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n50: | UI framework | Vue 3 + TypeScript | Type-safe components that mirror Frappe shapes |\n51: | Router | Vue Router 4 | File-based routing, SSR-ready |\n52: | Server | Vite 8 | Fast HMR, production build |\n53: | Styling | Tailwind CSS v4 + frappe-ui | Rapid design-system iteration, Frappe design tokens |\n54: | State / data | In-memory mock store (`src/mock-data/`) | No backend needed for prototype |\n55: | Dev tooling | Node.js, Vite 8, ESLint, Prettier | Fast iteration |\n56: \n57: **Important:** there is no database, no auth, no external API call in this prototype. A full page reload resets all in-memory state to the seeded mock data.\n58: \n59: ---\n60: \n61: ## 2. What this will become\n62: \n63: The production system will be built on the **Frappe Framework**, composing:\n64: \n65: | App | Role |\n66: |---|---|\n67: | [`frappe/frappe`](https://github.com/frappe/frappe) | Platform: auth, ORM, REST, jobs, audit log |\n68: | [`frappe/gameplan`](https://github.com/frappe/gameplan) | Community: Teams, Spaces (Projects), Posts (Discussions), Comments, Reactions |\n69: | [`frappe/lms`](https://github.com/frappe/lms) | Learning: Courses, Chapters, Lessons, Quizzes, Certificates |\n70: | [`frappe/raven`](https://github.com/The-Commit-Company/Raven) | Direct messaging + channels |\n71: | [`frappe/helpdesk`](https://github.com/frappe/helpdesk) | Member support + safeguarding triage |\n72: | [`frappe/wiki`](https://github.com/frappe/wiki) | Community handbook, code of conduct |\n73: | [`frappe/insights`](https://github.com/frappe/insights) | Analytics dashboards |\n74: | [`frappe/eps`](https://github.com/frappe/eps) | Gamification / Energy Points |\n75: | `fg_companion` *(new, ~1,500 lines Python)* | Events, mentor matching, AI hooks, moderation, polls, badges |\n76: \n77: The prototype's TypeScript types in [`src/mock-data/types.ts`](src/mock-data/types.ts) are **deliberately 1:1 with real Frappe DocType field names**. The porting work is a data-layer swap, not a redesign. See [`docs/03_PORTING_GUIDE.md`](docs/03_PORTING_GUIDE.md) and [`docs/04_FRAPPE_TRANSLATION.md`](docs/04_FRAPPE_TRANSLATION.md).\n78: \n79: ---\n80: \n81: ## 3. Running it right now\n82: \n83: ### Prerequisites\n84: \n85: | Tool | Minimum version | Check |\n86: |---|---|---|\n87: | [Node.js](https://nodejs.org) | 20 LTS | `node -v` |\n88: | Git | any recent | `git --version` |\n89: \n90: ### Clone & install\n91: \n92: ```bash\n93: git clone https://github.com/andiekobbietks/community-launchpad-proto.git\n94: cd community-launchpad-proto\n95: npm install\n96: ```\n97: \n98: ### Start the dev server\n99: \n100: ```bash\n101: npm run dev\n102: ```\n103: \n104: Open [http://localhost:8080](http://localhost:8080). Hot-module replacement is enabled — file saves are reflected instantly.\n105: \n106: ### Available scripts\n107: \n108: | Script | What it does |\n109: |---|---|\n110: | `npm run dev` | Starts Vite dev server with HMR on port 8080 |\n111: | `npm run build` | Production build |\n112: | `npm run build:dev` | Dev-mode build (useful for debugging) |\n113: | `npm run preview` | Serves the production build locally |\n114: | `npm run lint` | ESLint across all TypeScript/Vue files |\n115: | `npm run format` | Prettier format all files |\n116: \n117: ### Resetting state\n118: \n119: The mock store is **in-memory only**. Any change you make (new post, RSVP, mentor request) lives only for the current browser tab session. A full page reload (`F5` / `⌘R`) restores the seed data exactly as committed.\n120: \n121: ### The walkthrough overlay\n122: \n123: When you first open the app you'll see a guided walkthrough overlay (`src/components/Walkthrough.tsx`). Click **Next** to step through all prototype screens, or click **Skip** to go straight to the home feed. The overlay stores its state in `sessionStorage` so it only shows once per browser tab.\n124: \n125: ### Navigating the prototype\n126: \n127: | Route | What you see |\n128: |---|---|\n129: | `/` | Home feed — posts from all joined Spaces, newest first |\n130: | `/spaces/:spaceId` | Single Space with post list + **New Post** composer |\n131: | `/posts/:postId` | Full post + threaded comments + \"Similar posts\" AI stub |\n132: | `/events` | Event card grid; click **RSVP** to mutate in-memory attendees |\n133: | `/mentors` | Request a mentor + view your current matches |\n134: | `/courses` | Course catalogue stub (real LMS: `frappe/lms`) |\n135: | `/members` | Member directory |\n136: | `/members/:userId` | Member profile — bio, posts, badges |\n137: | `/messages` | DM thread list (Raven prototype) |\n138: | `/messages/:threadId` | Single DM conversation |\n139: | `/notifications` | Notification inbox |\n140: | `/settings` | Full settings panel — notifications, privacy, integrations, AI |\n141: | `/docs` | In-app documentation panel |\n142: \n143: ---\n144: \n145: ## 4. Architecture overview\n146: \n147: ```\n148: ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n149: │                   Browser (Vue 3 + Vue Router 4)                     │\n\n(Showing lines 50-149 of 790. Use offset=150 to continue.)\n</content>",
