      "type": "answer",
      "text": "Perfect! Now I can see the real project! You have the **FirstGens Community Platform Prototype** at `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\community-launchpad-proto`.\n\nThe key component is the `fg_companion` Python package that will become a Frappe app:\n\n## This is your Frappe app! (`fg_companion/`)\n\n**Current structure:**\n```\nC:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\community-launchpad-proto/\n├── fg_companion/           ← **Frappe app that needs setup**\n│   ├── pyproject.toml     ← Project config\n│   └── requirements.txt   ← Dependencies (onnxruntime, numpy)\n├── src/                    ← Vue 3 + TypeScript frontend\n└── docs/                   ← Documentation\n```\n\n## Fix Your Frappe App Setup:\n\nThe `fg_companion` project needs to be properly initialized as a Frappe app. Here's what you need to do:\n\n```bash\n# Navigate to your Frappe Bench directory\ncd /home/andiekobbie/frappe-bench\n\n# 1. Stop Frappe services (if available)\nbench restart || echo \"No running services\"\n\n# 2. Remove any broken app with similar name\nrm -rf /home/andiekobbie/frappe-bench/apps/fg_companion\n\n# 3. Create the Frappe app properly (remove --no-git)\nbench new-app fg_companion\n\n# 4. When prompted, use:\n# App Title: Fg Companion\n# App Description: Events, Mentors, AI sentiment & vector search for FirstGens Community\n# Publisher: FirstGens\n# Email: admin@firstgens.test\n# License: mit\n# Frappe Version: version-15\n# Install now: y\n\n# 5. Install the app\nbench --site firstgens.localhost install-app fg_companion\n\n# 6. Start services\nbench start\n```\n\n## Key Points:\n\n1. **Don't use `--no-git`** - It prevents proper app initialization\n2. **Use version 15** - It's the current supported version\n3. **Copy your `fg_companion` project** to the Frappe app location: `/home/andiekobbie/frappe-bench/apps/fg_companion/`\n\nThis will set up your Frappe app for the FirstGens Community platform! The frontend prototype will connect to the Frappe backend to create a complete community platform.\n\nDoes this clarify what needs to be fixed? The `fg_companion` directory is your Frappe app that needs proper setup!",
