      "text": "You're absolutely right to ask about this! Frappe has changed significantly, and **Frappe v11 is outdated and end-of-life**.\n\n## ❌ Current Issue: Frappe v11 (Old)\n\nFrom our earlier logs, we saw:\n```\n$ uv pip install --quiet -e /home/andiekobbie/frappe-bench/apps/fg_firstgens_app\nError: Frappe version-15\n```\n\nThe app was created with v11, which has problems:\n- **No longer supported** - v11 reached end-of-life\n- **Missing modern features** - API improvements, better UX\n- **Security vulnerabilities** in the underlying framework\n- **Incompatible commands** - `bench stop` doesn't exist in v11\n\n## ✅ Recommended: Frappe v15+ (Current)\n\n**Why v15 is better:**\n- **Latest features** - Modern APIs, better performance\n- **Active support** - Regular updates and security patches\n- **Community** - Larger ecosystem and documentation\n- **Modern tooling** - Better developer experience\n\n## 🔧 Fix Your Version:\n\n**When creating your Frappe app, explicitly use v15:**\n\n```bash\n# Create app with CURRENT version\ncd /home/andiekobbie/frappe-bench\nbench new-app fg_companion\n\n# When prompted, use:\n# Frappe Version: version-15  (Recommended)\n```\n\n**Alternative: Force upgrade existing app:**\n\n```bash\ncd /home/andiekobbie/frappe-bench/apps/fg_companion\n# Modify pyproject.toml to use frappe>=15\n```\n\n## 📋 Best Practice:\n\n```bash\n# Always create new apps with latest version\nbench new-app app-name\n\n# Use version-15 for new projects\n# Accept all defaults except Frappe Version\n```\n\n**Bottom line:** Yes, Frappe has been **upgraded and is good** in v15+, but your current setup is using outdated v11. The fix is to create your Frappe apps with version-15 from now on!\n\nIs this clear? Your Frappe setup needs a version upgrade from v11 to v15+ for modern features and security.",
