      "output": "?? Frappe Bench Installation for Ubuntu 24.04 (noble)\r\n-ForegroundColor\r\nYellow\r\n\nThe error above shows that Ubuntu 24.04 has external Python package protection.\nThis is normal and we need to use the correct approach.\n\n=== SOLUTION: Virtual Environment ===\n\n1. Create a virtual environment for Python:\n   python3 -m venv ~/frappe-bench_env\n\n2. Activate the virtual environment:\n   source ~/frappe-bench_env/bin/activate\n\n3. Install frappe-bench within the virtual environment:\n   pip install frappe-bench\n\n4. Set up Frappe Bench with virtual environment:\n   # Modify PATH in your shell profile or use the full path\n   export PATH=~/frappe-bench_env/bin:\n\n=== ALTERNATIVE: Ubuntu Package ===\n\nYou can install frappe-bench via Ubuntu package manager:\n   sudo apt install frappe-bench\n\nThen use the standard commands:\n\n   cd ~/frappe-bench\n   bench init -v version-15 myproject\n\n=== QUICK FIX: Override with --break-system-packages ===\n\nIf you want to continue with system Python:\n   pip3 install frappe-bench --break-system-packages\n\nThis will work but may have compatibility issues.\n\nRecommended approach: Use virtual environment for best compatibility.\n",
