igate and create your Frappe app:\\\" -ForegroundColor Gray\\nWrite-Host \\\"   cd myproject\\\" -ForegroundColor Gray\\nWrite-Host \\\"   source ~/frappe-bench_env/bin/activate && bench new-app fg_companion\\\" -ForegroundColor Gray\\nWrite-Host \\\"\\\"\\nWrite-Host \\\"=== ALTERNATIVE: Use Ubuntu Package ===\\\" -ForegroundColor Green\\nWrite-Host \\\"\\\"\\nWrite-Host \\\"You can install frappe-bench via apt (recommended for beginners):\\\" -ForegroundColor Gray\\nWrite-Host \\\"   sudo apt update && sudo apt install frappe-bench\\\" -ForegroundColor Gray\\nWrite-Host \\\"\\\"\\nWrite-Host \\\"Then:\\n   cd ~/frappe-benge\\\" -ForegroundColor Gray\\nWrite-Host \\\"   bench init -v version-15 myproject\\\" -ForegroundColor Gray\", \"description\": \"Provide quick fix commands for virtual environment setup\"}",
      "output": "?? SOLUTION: Virtual Environment Setup\r\n-ForegroundColor\r\nGreen\r\n\nStep 1: Create a virtual environment for Frappe Bench:\n   python3 -m venv ~/frappe-bench_env\n\nStep 2: Activate the virtual environment:\n   source ~/frappe-bench_env/bin/activate\n\nStep 3: Install frappe-bench within the virtual environment:\n   pip install frappe-bench\n\nStep 4: Make frappe-bench available globally (optional):\n   cd ~/frappe-bench\n   bench init -v version-15 myproject\n\n=== QUICK COMMANDS ===\n\nRun these commands to set up everything:\n\n(1) Create virtual environment:\n   python3 -m venv ~/frappe-bench_env\n\n(2) Install frappe-bench:\n   source ~/frappe-bench_env/bin/activate && pip install frappe-bench\n\n(3) Test installation:\n   source ~/frappe-bench_env/bin/activate && bench --version\n\n(4) Create your app:\n   source ~/frappe-bench_env/bin/activate && bench init -v version-15 myproject\n\n(5) Navigate and create your Frappe app:\n   cd myproject\n   source ~/frappe-bench_env/bin/activate && bench new-app fg_companion\n\n=== ALTERNATIVE: Use Ubuntu Package ===\n\nYou can install frappe-bench via apt (recommended for beginners):\n   sudo apt update && sudo apt install frappe-bench\n\nThen:\n   cd ~/frappe-benge\n   bench init -v version-15 myproject\n",
