      "type": "answer",
      "text": "I see you're having terminal/shell compatibility issues. Let me provide you with the **simplest working solution**:\n\n## 🔄 **RESET & START FRESH:**\n\n### Step 1: Close your current terminal and open a new bash terminal\n```bash\n# Close your current terminal and open a fresh bash terminal in WSL\ncd ~/frappe-bench\n```\n\n### Step 2: Create virtual environment\n```bash\npython3 -m venv env\nsource env/bin/activate\n```\n\n### Step 3: Install frappe-bench\n```bash\npip install frappe-bench\n```\n\n### Step 4: Initialize Frappe Bench\n```bash\ncd ~/frappe-bench\nbench init -v version-15 myproject\n```\n\n### Step 5: Create your Frappe app\n```bash\ncd myproject\nsource ../env/bin/activate\nbench new-app fg_companion\n```\n\n**When prompted, use these values:**\n- **Frappe Version:** version-15 (Recommended)\n- **App Title:** Fg Companion\n- **App Description:** Events, Mentors, AI sentiment & vector search for FirstGens Community\n- **Publisher:** FirstGens\n- **Email:** admin@firstgens.test\n\n### Step 6: Install and Start\n```bash\nbench --site firstgens.localhost install-app fg_companion\nbench start\n```\n\n## ⚠️ **Important Note:**\nThe shell issues you're experiencing suggest you might be using PowerShell instead of bash. **WSL requires a proper bash terminal** for these commands to work correctly.\n\n**To fix:** Close your current terminal and open a fresh bash terminal, then run these commands one by one. This will avoid any shell compatibility issues.\n\nDoes this help get you started with a fresh Frappe Bench setup?",
